author: newsroom@capegazette.com (Staff)
title: Beacon hockey beats Dover Central 3-1 in battle of unbeaten teams
text:
Beacon hockey beats Dover Central 3-1 in battle of unbeaten teams Oct 15, 2015 Photo by: Dave Frederick Alex Wilson looks to put the orange ball in the back of the cage. 
The Beacon field hockey juggernaut was in a closely contested, emotional game for 50 minutes against previously unbeaten Dover Central Oct. 12 at Beacon and emerged with a 3-1 victory. 
First-half Beacon goals were scored by Alex Wilson and Lola Messick. Timesha Cannon scored in the second half for Beacon. 
Beacon goaltending duties were shared by Autumn Davis and Marlee Geppert. Ryleigh Elliott of Beacon battles in the midfield. (Photo by: Dave Frederick ) Dover defenders fly on on corner defense. (Photo by: Dave Frederick ) Anna Stancofski is a defensive stalwart for Beacon. (Photo by: Dave Frederick )
